This describes how to setup the mempol2 dev environment


* install django, couchdb & python bindings

    sudo apt-get install python-django couchdb python-anyjson python-memcache python-couchdb



--- OUTDATED

* install restkit and couchdbkit

    NOTE: restkit is not in debian squeeze as of now, and the couchdbkit version
    that is provided didn't work against a recent restkit, so I got both
    from git (stefan 2010-03-18)


    git clone git://github.com/benoitc/restkit.git
    cd couchdbkit
    git checkout 1.2.1
    sudo python2.6 ./setup.py install


    git clone git://github.com/benoitc/couchdbkit.git
    cd couchdbkit
    git checkout 0.4.5
    sudo python2.6 ./setup.py install


* install the tornado web server

instructions copied from http://www.tornadoweb.org/

sudo apt-get install python-dev python-pycurl python-simplejson
wget http://www.tornadoweb.org/static/tornado-0.2.tar.gz
tar xvzf tornado-0.2.tar.gz
cd tornado-0.2
python setup.py build
sudo python setup.py install
